news.title: NGPDA adopts land use map of Panaji
news.para: The land use map and register were accepted by the town and country planning board on November 10 after making some modifications in the land use register.

news.title: Over 55 lakh people have received houses in last six years: Uttar Pradesh CM
news.para: The chief minister made the remarks while inaugurating and laying the foundation stone of 116 development works worth Rs 175 crore at Yogiraj Baba Gambhirnath Auditorium in Gorakhpur, the UP government said in a statement.

news.title: How cut in registration fees will cost home-buyers more in Tamil Nadu
news.para: Home-buyers and developers had hitherto been registering a sale deed of undivided share (UDS) of the land and a construction agreement for the built-up area in case of flats/apartments.

news.title: Pune metro stretch to Ramwadi up for launch in December 2023
news.para: The Maha Metro has started speed trials of rakes till Ramwadi, for which technical teams are checking the alignment of tracks, curves, elevation and other technical parameters, such as signalling and telecommunication.

news.title: Builders must take prompt action to help improve air quality: Panvel civic body
news.para: The civic officials have been instructed to visit construction sites and pass on the guidelines towards marginalising the pollution level in the neighbourhood.

news.title: Karnataka government plans B Khata for properties in ULBs of tier-II cities
news.para: While discussing the implementation of Jalasiri, the 24x 7 drinking water project, Suresh expressed displeasure over not taking up measures for additional water augmentation.

news.title: Ludhiana civic body team razes illegal colony in Kailash Nagar
news.para: A few structures were also being raised in the colony, which have been demolished by the civic body team. As per officials, legal proceedings were also being initiated against the coloniser.

news.title: Ludhiana: Drive to recover property tax begins, 'golden' chance on offer
news.para: Officials of the municipal corporation (MC) are trying to convince them to clear their dues as there is a chance that no interest and penalty would be levied and they must avail the opportunity.

news.title: Nagpur civic body attaches 225 plots of property tax defaulters
news.para: Pushpagandha Bhagat, deputy commissioner of Hanuman Nagar zone, said 58 plots belonged to Shewanta Co-operative Housing Society Limited, 63 to Suvikas Co-operative Housing Society Limited and 104 plots to Gangotri Developers. All these plots were located in Hudkeshwar area.

news.title: Urban development minister to review promenade project in Mangaluru
news.para: At a review meeting held at the Mangaluru City Corporation (MCC) here on Friday, the minister said that he will review the proposal.

news.title: DDA needs more time to hand over in situ EWS flats in North Delhi
news.para: Officials said the finishing work was put on hold due to the enforcement of Graded Response Action Plan (GRAP)-IV due to deteriorating air quality, and the flats would now be ready in January.

news.title: GMRC soon? Gurugram metro expansion set to get push
news.para: According to state government sources, the central government is providing financial assistance for the proposed metro expansion plan and to have equity in the project, it was required to create a new separate entity with its own account book.

news.title: Centrum Group ropes in EY to find buyers for its stake in housing arm
news.para: The Jaspal Bindra-led group plans to either exit the housing finance business fully or pare stake to become a minority shareholder.

news.title: PNB Housing Finance to raise Rs 3,500 crore via NCDs
news.para: The NCD will be raised on a private placement basis, PNB Housing Finance said in a regulatory filing.

news.title: ED conducts multi-state raids against Shine City Properties in money-laundering case
news.para: ​The action is being carried out against Shine City Properties Ltd. and those linked to it in a fraud investment scheme estimated at Rs 800 crore, they said.

news.title: Amitabh Bachchan gifts bungalow valued at Rs 50.63 crore to daughter Shweta Nanda
news.para: According to the documents accessed from property registration data aggregator Zapkey(dot)com, Bachchan executed the transfer of the bungalow on November 9 as a gift to his daughter and paid Rs 50.65 lakh as stamp duty.

news.title: Seven years gone, no Gurugram civic body's takeover; now, DLF hikes upkeep fee
news.para: Instead, DLF has now increased common area maintenance charges by 50 paise per square yard, which amounts to a hike of Rs 1,500 per quarter for a plot measuring 1,000 square yards.

news.title: Reliance Nippon Life renews lease for 48,924 sq ft office in Inspire BKC
news.para: The company has leased the office space from the landlord Adani Realty for a total tenure of five years. The agreement includes a lock-in period for the tenant for the entire term of the lease.

news.title: Ireland's central bank says commercial real estate price shock orderly so far
news.para: The regulator said that while commercial real estate prices have dropped by more than 20% since mid-2020 and may have further to fall, the transmission of the price shock to the domestic financial system has been orderly "up to now".

news.title: Swedish property company SBB to buy back $440 million of debt
news.para: SBB has agreed to buy back 417.2 million euros of its debt for 403.8 million euros, SBB said, having previously announced a purchase up to a maximum of 600 million euros.
